The paper deals with representation learning from multiple views, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The dataset used in the paper contains video and sound, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). The use of automatic captions and textual modalities suggests that it could also belong to "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper deals with multimodal data, which suggests that it could also belong to "Multimedia" (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of the learned representations on retrieval-based tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
